sections.text:
(A) Investigations and consideration of the commission shall include, but are not limited to, the following areas:

(1) knowledge of the institution;

(2) ethical fitness;

(3) professional and academic ability;

(4) character;

(5) reputation;

(6) physical health;

(7) mental stability;

(8) experience; and

(9) demonstrated support of and involvement in the institution.

(B) In making nominations, race, gender, national origin, and other demographic factors must be considered by the commission.

HISTORY: 2017 Act No. 17 (S.213), Section 1, eff May 9, 2017.
